cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CE, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the application of data reconciliation and principal component analysis in process industries, which involves analyzing large amounts of data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) which deals with data analysis and modeling. The paper also discusses the use of PCA as a preprocessing technique for denoising measurements, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of PCA in reducing the dimensionality of high dimensional data, which is a common problem in data science and falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of DR and PCA in dealing with partially measured systems, which falls under the category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the paper discusses the deployment of DR and PCA together in a collaborative and consistent manner, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
